o.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:  A DIFFERENT way to roleplay a paladin</span><hr size=1> Hi, I don't mean to impune your role-playing ability or choices, and I'm not jumping on you personaly, I just disagree with your thoughts. This is all from an RP standpoint too. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>There is no other way to play a Paladin. Paladins are holy warriors, fighters for their cause. The fight without doubt, or confusion, and they serve their diety to the fullest. The last thing a Paladin will ever do is question his or her faith. To do so makes you less. When you are a Paladin, you are the living embodyment of your God. I am a beloved of Erollisi Marr. Erollisi is love, and so am I. I love everyone. No call for help goes unheeded, no request for aid is ignored, and no pity is spared.<br>Love is the force that binds us all together. Love it the only magic that can heal your heart, bind your soul to another, or create the finest things in all of Norrath and Luclin. Love is the master I serve, and to question love, to give in to hate, to acknowledge fear or loathing would defeat the whole point of being a Paladin of Erollisi.<br>I do not question my faith. <br>I do not give in to hate, fear, or malace.<br>I show everyone the power and glory of love.<br><br>That is the way to play a Paladin. <br><br>Cephany Lopod<br>Paladin of Erollisi <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udefymortality.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Defy Mortality</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/28/02 7:50:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgodsmightroleplaytavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=117.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:  A DIFFERENT way to roleplay a paladin</span><hr size=1> aye, if yer faith is shaken, and not total, then you lose your paladin powers roleplaying wise.<br><br>Roleplaying wise it's ok, like in a d&amp;d game, where you'd have to face the consequences of losing your powers, and have to do some quest/deed to regain them.<br><br>but in eq, it's not so solid.<br><br>Not saying that faith is never shaken, paladins do lose faith, but they do regain it, and redeem themselves, etc.<br>But if he's starting to trust dark elf necromancers, that gets a little wierd.<br><br>also that means the necro isn't roleplaying right =P <p><small><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=145574">Kahlin Cagn</a><br><b>Destitute Gnome Paladin</small></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugilfalas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gilfalas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 1505<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/29/02 9:09:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgodsmightroleplaytavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=117.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:  A DIFFERENT way to roleplay a paladin</span><hr size=1> I call this the Drizzt/Twinkie fator. Everyone wants to play that cool evil race and be a mean badass but they want to be a goodguy too so they don't have to suffer the consequences of playing a bad guy.<br><br>Basically they want the best of all worlds. One of my personal pet peeves.<br><br>I have not YET run into a DE in EQ (Except my